fastPathDnsResControlMIB.name: fastPathDnsResControlMIB

revisions.description: DNS Client Source Interface related changes.
Initial version of this MIB module.

fastPathDnsResControlMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP MIB under the Broadcom Inc enterprise OID pertaining to DNS Client control configuration

DnsCacheEntryType.name: DnsCacheEntryType
DnsCacheEntryType.description: A DNS cache entry type. This is for address or for canonical name.

agentResCtlAdminMode.name: agentResCtlAdminMode
agentResCtlAdminMode.description: The dns client administrative modes supported by the device. The dns client services can be turned on or off.

agentResCtlDefDomainName.name: agentResCtlDefDomainName
agentResCtlDefDomainName.description: The default domain name for unqualified hostnames.

agentResCtlCacheFlushStatus.name: agentResCtlCacheFlushStatus
agentResCtlCacheFlushStatus.description: The cache Flush status. If set to enable all dynamic cache entries would be removed.

agentResCtlRequestTimeout.name: agentResCtlRequestTimeout
agentResCtlRequestTimeout.description: The timeout before retransmitting a request to the server. The timeout value is configured and displayed in seconds.

agentResCtlRequestRetransmits.name: agentResCtlRequestRetransmits
agentResCtlRequestRetransmits.description: The number of times the request is retransmitted. The request is retransmitted provided the maximum timeout value allows this many number of retransmits.

agentResCtlDomainListTable.name: agentResCtlDomainListTable
agentResCtlDomainListTable.description: A table for default domain list.

agentResCtlDomainListEntry.name: agentResCtlDomainListEntry
agentResCtlDomainListEntry.description: An entry in the DNS domain name list. Rows may be created or deleted at any time by the DNS Resolver and by SNMP SET requests.

agentResCtlDomainListName.name: agentResCtlDomainListName
agentResCtlDomainListName.description: The dns domain list entry identified by this row of the table.

agentResCtlDomainListNameStatus.name: agentResCtlDomainListNameStatus
agentResCtlDomainListNameStatus.description: Status of the DNS domain list Entry Table Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentResCtlConfigIPEntry.name: agentResCtlConfigIPEntry
agentResCtlConfigIPEntry.description: An entry in the DNS Servers list. Rows may be created or deleted at any time by the DNS Resolver and by SNMP SET requests.

agentResCtlDnsNameServerIPType.name: agentResCtlDnsNameServerIPType
agentResCtlDnsNameServerIPType.description: The Type of IP address of the dns server identified by this row of the table. Can be either ipv4(1), or ipv6(2).

agentResCtlDnsNameServerIP.name: agentResCtlDnsNameServerIP
agentResCtlDnsNameServerIP.description: The IP address of the dns server identified by this row of the table.

agentResCtlDnsNameServerStatus.name: agentResCtlDnsNameServerStatus
agentResCtlDnsNameServerStatus.description: Status of the DNS Server Address Table Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentResCtlStaticServConfigTable.name: agentResCtlStaticServConfigTable
agentResCtlStaticServConfigTable.description: Static table of DNS hostname to IP address table

agentResCtlStaticServEntry.name: agentResCtlStaticServEntry
agentResCtlStaticServEntry.description: An entry in the static DNS hostname IP address list. Rows may be created or deleted at any time by the DNS Resolver and by SNMP SET requests.

agentResCtlStaticHostName.name: agentResCtlStaticHostName
agentResCtlStaticHostName.description: The static hostname to be stored in the name server table.

agentResCtlStaticIPAddress.name: agentResCtlStaticIPAddress
agentResCtlStaticIPAddress.description: The IP address of the dns server for the static hostname.

agentResCtlStaticNameServerStatus.name: agentResCtlStaticNameServerStatus
agentResCtlStaticNameServerStatus.description: Status of the Static Host Name - IP Address Table Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentResCtlSourceInterface.name: agentResCtlSourceInterface
agentResCtlSourceInterface.description: A source-interface selection on an Interface Index (like vlan based routing interface, port based routing interface, loopback interface, tunnel interface). A non-zero value indicates ifIndex for the corresponding interface entry in the ifTable is selected. A zero value indicates the source-interface un-selection.
